Manchester United boss, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer, has named his side’s starting XI against Sheffield United in the Premier League on Wednesday evening. Solskjaer opted to start midfielder Paul Pogba, against the visitors at Old Trafford. The Norwagian released the list in a post via Man United’s official Twitter page. Man United starting XI against Sheffield: De Gea, Wan-Bissaka, Lindelof, Maguire, Shaw, Matic, Pogba, Greenwood, Fernandes, Rashford and Martial Substitutes: Ighalo, Romero, Baily, Williams, Andreas, Fred, James, Mata, McTominay. The kick-off time for the match is 6 pm